PFx: Imagine you have a tiny water balloon inside your tummy. This balloon is called a peritoneal cyst. It sits quietly in a soft covering around your stomach and other parts, like your intestines. These cysts are usually no big deal. You probably won’t even notice them, and they do not hurt. Sometimes doctors find them when they look at your belly for other reasons. Usually, you don’t have to do anything about them. They just stay there, like a small, still balloon, not causing any trouble. So, there's no need to be concerned.

A simple hydrosalpinx is when fluid fills one of the tubes that connects the ovaries to the womb. Picture a straw, usually empty, but now has fluid inside. It shows up on scans looking a bit puffed up. This is not usually painful or dangerous, and people often don’t notice it. Sometimes, it happens because of old infections, but usually, it’s found by accident during exams for something else. It's mostly nothing to stress about as it doesn’t typically cause problems.

An ovarian fibroma is a small growth on an ovary. An ovary is a part of the female body involved in baby-making. This growth is not cancer, which means it's safe and won't spread. Often, it doesn't cause pain or problems, so many people don't even know it's there. Doctors usually find ovarian fibromas by surprise when looking at something else. While they are generally harmless, knowing about them is useful in case they start to cause problems later. Think of it like a tiny bump that is usually no big deal.

An endometrioma is a type of cyst that grows on the ovary. It's like a small bubble or balloon inside your body. This bubble contains tissue that usually grows inside the uterus, but it ends up outside. Sometimes, it fills with thick, dark fluid, kind of like chocolate. Usually, people don't know they have it, because it might not hurt. But sometimes it can cause pain or other issues. Doctors might find it by accident when checking for something else. It's like finding a tiny surprise during a health check.

An ovarian dermoid is a special kind of cyst in your ovaries, which are the parts of a woman's body that help make babies. These cysts are like little bubbles that can have surprising things in them, like hair or teeth. They aren't there when you're born but can grow over time. Most of the time, these cysts aren't dangerous and don't become cancer. Even though they might seem strange, they usually don't cause any harm. It's like finding a small surprise inside you, but not one that should make you worried.
